verses.text_plain: Rebuke not an elder, but intreat him as a father; and the younger men as brethren;
verses.verse_html: 1Rebuke not an elder, but intreat him as a father; and the younger men as brethren;

verses.text_plain: The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, with all purity.
verses.verse_html: 2The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, with all purity.

verses.text_plain: Honour widows that are widows indeed.
verses.verse_html: 3Honour widows that are widows indeed.

verses.text_plain: But if any widow have children or nephews, let them learn first to shew piety at home, and to requite their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.
verses.verse_html: 4But if any widow have children or nephews, let them learn first to shew piety at home, and to requite their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.

verses.text_plain: Now she that is a widow indeed, and desolate, trusteth in God, and continueth in supplications and prayers night and day.
verses.verse_html: 5Now she that is a widow indeed, and desolate, trusteth in God, and continueth in supplications and prayers night and day.

verses.text_plain: But she that liveth in pleasure is dead while she liveth.
verses.verse_html: 6But she that liveth in pleasure is dead while she liveth.

verses.text_plain: And these things give in charge, that they may be blameless.
verses.verse_html: 7And these things give in charge, that they may be blameless.

verses.text_plain: But if any provide not for his own, and specially for those of his own house, he hath denied the faith, and is worse than an infidel.
verses.verse_html: 8But if any provide not for his own, and specially for those of his own house, he hath denied the faith, and is worse than an infidel.

tokens.text: for those of his own house

verses.text_plain: Let not a widow be taken into the number under threescore years old, having been the wife of one man,
verses.verse_html: 9Let not a widow be taken into the number under threescore years old, having been the wife of one man,

verses.text_plain: Well reported of for good works; if she have brought up children, if she have lodged strangers, if she have washed the saints’ feet, if she have relieved the afflicted, if she have diligently followed every good work.
verses.verse_html: 10Well reported of for good works; if she have brought up children, if she have lodged strangers, if she have washed the saints’ feet, if she have relieved the afflicted, if she have diligently followed every good work.

verses.text_plain: But the younger widows refuse: for when they have begun to wax wanton against Christ, they will marry;
verses.verse_html: 11But the younger widows refuse: for when they have begun to wax wanton against Christ, they will marry;

tokens.text: they have begun to wax wanton against

verses.text_plain: Having damnation, because they have cast off their first faith.
verses.verse_html: 12Having damnation, because they have cast off their first faith.

verses.text_plain: And withal they learn to be idle, wandering about from house to house; and not only idle, but tattlers also and busybodies, speaking things which they ought not.
verses.verse_html: 13And withal they learn to be idle, wandering about from house to house; and not only idle, but tattlers also and busybodies, speaking things which they ought not.

verses.text_plain: I will therefore that the younger women marry, bear children, guide the house, give none occasion to the adversary to speak reproachfully.
verses.verse_html: 14I will therefore that the younger women marry, bear children, guide the house, give none occasion to the adversary to speak reproachfully.

verses.text_plain: For some are already turned aside after Satan.
verses.verse_html: 15For some are already turned aside after Satan.

verses.text_plain: If any man or woman that believeth have widows, let them relieve them, and let not the church be charged; that it may relieve them that are widows indeed.
verses.verse_html: 16If any man or woman that believeth have widows, let them relieve them, and let not the church be charged; that it may relieve them that are widows indeed.

verses.text_plain: Let the elders that rule well be counted worthy of double honour, especially they who labour in the word and doctrine.
verses.verse_html: 17 Let the elders that rule well be counted worthy of double honour, especially they who labour in the word and doctrine.

verses.text_plain: For the scripture saith, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox that treadeth out the corn. And, The labourer is worthy of his reward.
verses.verse_html: 18For the scripture saith, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox that treadeth out the corn. And, The labourer is worthy of his reward.

verses.text_plain: Against an elder receive not an accusation, but before two or three witnesses.
verses.verse_html: 19Against an elder receive not an accusation, but before two or three witnesses.

verses.text_plain: Them that sin rebuke before all, that others also may fear.
verses.verse_html: 20Them that sin rebuke before all, that others also may fear.

verses.text_plain: I charge thee before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, and the elect angels, that thou observe these things without preferring one before another, doing nothing by partiality.
verses.verse_html: 21I charge thee before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, and the elect angels, that thou observe these things without preferring one before another, doing nothing by partiality.

verses.text_plain: Lay hands suddenly on no man, neither be partaker of other men’s sins: keep thyself pure.
verses.verse_html: 22Lay hands suddenly on no man, neither be partaker of other men’s sins: keep thyself pure.

verses.text_plain: Drink no longer water, but use a little wine for thy stomach’s sake and thine often infirmities.
verses.verse_html: 23 Drink no longer water, but use a little wine for thy stomach’s sake and thine often infirmities.

verses.text_plain: Some men’s sins are open beforehand, going before to judgment; and some men they follow after.
verses.verse_html: 24Some men’s sins are open beforehand, going before to judgment; and some men they follow after.

verses.text_plain: Likewise also the good works of some are manifest beforehand; and they that are otherwise cannot be hid.
verses.verse_html: 25Likewise also the good works of some are manifest beforehand; and they that are otherwise cannot be hid.
